actual.comment:
The Promise of Sydney contains commitments from several GEF-eligible countries. Of these, the project is supporting initiatives in an initial selection of countries:

-	Colombia: commitment to system-level governance assessment; adoption of global PA standards that incorporate PA governance and PA management effectiveness; sub-national examination of incentives (legal, policy) for PA establishment;

-	Kenya commitment to system-level governance assessment; adoption of global PA standards; examination of private PAs as part of system.

-	Mexico: climate change and PA strategy integration; adoption of global PA standards;

-	Peru: commitment to examine private Pas as part of PA system governance; commitment to develop learning on new sources of PA finance, including impact investment.

-	Indonesia: commitment to address gaps in marine PA governance at system-level; commitment to no-take and adoption of PA governance materials at national / curriculum level.

-	PNG: civil society and government collaboration on outreach and PA planning tolos that focus on indigenous and local ecological knowledge as a key determinant of PA values and operations

-	Republic of Marshall Islands: commitment to adopt PA solutions template; examine role of island and atoll MPAs as part of PA system; 

-	China: adoption of global PA standards and integration of IUCN PA Categories at system-level.

