baseline.comment:
Baseline 1: Limited capacities of GFP’s in MoD’s to mainstream gender equality in defense policies and practices;
Baseline 2: Poor gender responsiveness of human resources policies in defense;
Baseline 3: Non existing gender sensitivisation programme for the military personnel.

indicator.description:
Indicator 1.1: Number of storage locations with improved security; 
Indicator 1.2: Number of people with increased capacity for ensuring security of stockpiles; 
Indicator 2: Number of surplus weapons and ammunition removed through destruction;
Indicator 3: Efficient marking, tracing and registration systems in place;
Indicator 4: Regional cooperation and standardization of polices, transfer of best-practices and information exchange through regional meetings;
Indicator 5: Number of collection campaigns of weapons or explosive devices (and assistance in the legalization of weapons in civilian possession through their registration).

baseline.comment:
Baseline 1: Inadequately secured storages;
Baseline 2: Significant surpluses of SALW and ammunition pose a threat to human security;
Baseline 3: Inadequate national registration, marking and tracing systems and capabilities;
Baseline 4: Limited regional cooperation and information sharing on SALW related issues;
Baseline 5: Significant numbers of illicit SALW and ammunition pose a threat to human security in the Western Balkans.
